<div class="entry-content clear" itemprop="text">
<div class="is-layout-constrained entry-content wp-block-post-content">
<div>
<p><strong><a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-سورة-النصر-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين-والنابلسي?page=862" > Surah An-Nasr </a> in a dream</strong> The Lord Almighty revealed <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-سورة-النصر-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين-والنابلسي?page=862" > Surah An-Nasr </a> to the Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him, as a message of reassurance and a promise of victory over enemies and disbelievers, so that the Islamic religion will become the prevalent religion among worshippers. God, and it expands and spreads to the farthest countries, so seeing this Surah in a dream is considered a sign of victory and the dreamer's ability to overcome the problems and differences he is going through, even if you are one of those who seek a legal interpretation of this vision, you can read the following lines on our website. </p>
<p><span></span></p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-سورة-النصر-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين-والنابلسي?page=862" > Surah An-Nasr </a> in a dream</strong></h2>
<p>If the dreamer is on the verge of a new position or authority that he will take up in his work, then seeing <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-سورة-النصر-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين-والنابلسي?page=862" > Surah An-Nasr </a> is considered good news for achieving more successes and achievements in this position, and therefore he will have many signs and influential additions that will raise his status among people, so he will have a word that is heard among them and he will preach to them and guide them to righteousness. </p>
<p>Some experts also stated that reading <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-سورة-النصر-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين-والنابلسي?page=862" > Surah An-Nasr </a> for the dreamer is an indication of his imminent death as a witness and his name is written with the messengers and the righteous, and this is often the case if he assumes a leadership position or one of the soldiers who joins the army to defend the homeland from wars and dangers, or the dream is taken as evidence of the death of one of his relatives after a long illness and great misery, and God knows best. </p><div class="angwp_84394 _ning_cont _ning_hidden _ning_outer _align_center responsive" data-aid="0" data-bid="84394" data-size="custom" style="max-width:100%; width:100%;height:inherit;"><div class="_ning_label _left" style=""></div><div class="_ning_inner" style=""><script type="text/javascript">
